cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.DS 

The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a problem commonly studied in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses classification and optimization, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper introduces a novel measurement with rigorous generalization bounds, which is related to sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
